#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="an3.127"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.127:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:0.2"
msgid "13. Kusināravagga "
msgstr "13. Kusināra "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.127:0.3"
msgid "127. Hatthakasutta "
msgstr "127. With Hatthaka "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an3.127:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho hatthako devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā: "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the glorious god Hatthaka, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha. Thinking, "

#. VAR: osīdatimeva saṃsīdatimeva → osīdati ceva saṃsīdati ca (bj) | osīdati saṃsīdati (s1-3, km) | osīdati ceva saṃsīdati ceva (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.127:1.3"
msgid "“bhagavato purato ṭhassāmī”ti osīdatimeva saṃsīdatimeva, na sakkoti saṇṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr "“I will stand before the Buddha,” he sank and melted down, and wasn’t able to stay still. "

msgctxt "an3.127:1.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma sappi vā telaṃ vā vālukāya āsittaṃ osīdatimeva saṃsīdatimeva, na saṇṭhāti; "
msgstr "It’s like when ghee or oil is poured on sand, it sinks and melts down, and can’t remain stable. "

msgctxt "an3.127:1.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ hatthako devaputto: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "an3.127:1.6"
msgid "“bhagavato purato ṭhassāmī”ti osīdatimeva saṃsīdatimeva, na sakkoti saṇṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli1.279, sc2
msgctxt "an3.127:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā hatthakaṃ devaputtaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Hatthaka, "

# NOTE: Cp DN 18, DN 19
msgctxt "an3.127:2.2"
msgid "“oḷārikaṃ, hatthaka, attabhāvaṃ abhinimmināhī”ti. "
msgstr "“Hatthaka, manifest in a solid life-form.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:2.3"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti, kho hatthako devaputto bhagavato paṭissutvā oḷārikaṃ attabhāvaṃ abhinimminitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” replied Hatthaka. He manifested in a solid life-form, bowed to the Buddha, and stood to one side. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:2.4"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho hatthakaṃ devaputtaṃ bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said to him, "

#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an3.127:3.1"
msgid "“Ye te, hatthaka, dhammā pubbe manussabhūtassa pavattino ahesuṃ, api nu te te dhammā etarahi pavattino”ti? "
msgstr "“Hatthaka, I wonder whether you still rehearse now the teachings that you rehearsed when you were a human being?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:3.2"
msgid "“Ye ca me, bhante, dhammā pubbe manussabhūtassa pavattino ahesuṃ, te ca me dhammā etarahi pavattino; "
msgstr "“I still rehearse now the teachings that I rehearsed as a human being. "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.3"
msgid "ye ca me, bhante, dhammā pubbe manussabhūtassa nappavattino ahesuṃ, te ca me dhammā etarahi pavattino. "
msgstr "And I also rehearse teachings that I didn’t rehearse as a human being. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:3.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhante, bhagavā etarahi ākiṇṇo viharati bhikkhūhi bhikkhunīhi upāsakehi upāsikāhi rājūhi rājamahāmattehi titthiyehi titthiyasāvakehi; "
msgstr "Just as the Buddha these days lives crowded by monks, nuns, laymen, and laywomen; by rulers and their ministers, and teachers of other paths and their disciples, "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.5"
msgid "evamevaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, ākiṇṇo viharāmi devaputtehi. "
msgstr "so I live crowded by the gods. "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.6"
msgid "Dūratopi, bhante, devaputtā āgacchanti hatthakassa devaputtassa santike ‘dhammaṃ sossāmā’ti. "
msgstr "The gods come from far away, thinking, ‘We’ll hear the teaching in the presence of Hatthaka.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.127:3.7"
msgid "Tiṇṇāhaṃ, bhante, dhammānaṃ atitto appaṭivāno kālaṅkato. "
msgstr "Sir, I passed away without getting enough of three things. "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.8"
msgid "Katamesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ? "
msgstr "What three? "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.9"
msgid "Bhagavato ahaṃ, bhante, dassanassa atitto appaṭivāno kālaṅkato; "
msgstr "Seeing the Buddha; "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.10"
msgid "saddhammasavanassāhaṃ, bhante, atitto appaṭivāno kālaṅkato; "
msgstr "hearing the true teaching; "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.11"
msgid "saṅghassāhaṃ, bhante, upaṭṭhānassa atitto appaṭivāno kālaṅkato. "
msgstr "and serving the Saṅgha. "

msgctxt "an3.127:3.12"
msgid "Imesaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhante, tiṇṇaṃ dhammānaṃ atitto appaṭivāno kālaṅkatoti. "
msgstr "I passed away without getting enough of these three things. "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc4
#. VAR: Nāhaṃ bhagavato → bhagavato (syā1-3)
msgctxt "an3.127:4.1"
msgid "Nāhaṃ bhagavato dassanassa, "
msgstr "I could never get enough "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Tittimajjhagā → titti addhā (s1-3) | tittiṃ ajjha (pts1) | titti tittisambhavaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.127:4.2"
msgid "Tittimajjhagā kudācanaṃ; "
msgstr "of seeing the Buddha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.127:4.3"
msgid "Saṃghassa upaṭṭhānassa, "
msgstr "serving the Saṅgha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.127:4.4"
msgid "Saddhammasavanassa ca. "
msgstr "or hearing the teaching. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "an3.127:5.1"
msgid "Adhisīlaṃ sikkhamāno, "
msgstr "Training in the higher ethics, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.127:5.2"
msgid "saddhammasavane rato; "
msgstr "loving to hear the true teaching, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.127:5.3"
msgid "Tiṇṇaṃ dhammānaṃ atitto, "
msgstr "Hatthaka has gone to the Aviha realm "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "an3.127:5.4"
msgid "hatthako avihaṃ gato”ti. "
msgstr "without getting enough of these three things.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.127:5.5"
msgid "Pañcamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

